item.description:
During my PhD, I got interested in the question:
&ldquo;How should you do cross-validation when facing shifts in your covariates and you have no labels for your target data?&rdquo;
Sugiyama&rsquo;s group has worked on this question extensively, and proposes a technique called &ldquo;importance-weighted cross-validation&rdquo;. I&rsquo;ve used this estimator before, but found that it behaves unusually in certain cases. That led me to start investigating the difference between the importance-weighted source risk estimator and the target risk estimator in greater detail.
